/-!
Direct semantic witness coverage.

The arrays below intentionally record only direct fixtures.  The full model
suite provides shared positive coverage for all registered axioms, but these
lists make it explicit which axioms already have small, targeted positive or
negative witnesses.  They are the checklist for the per-axiom backfill.

Negative coverage is section-by-section and every axiom must be classified in
exactly one of:

* `directNegativeWitnessAxioms`: a fixture whose first confirmed semantic
  failure is this axiom;
* `compilerEnforcedNegativeAxioms`: no direct DSL counterexample is expected
  because the compiler/finite semantics enforces the condition before
  certification;
* `blockedNegativeWitnessAxioms`: a principled negative witness still needs
  surface syntax, extractor support, or a smaller first-failure isolating model.
-/

def directPositiveWitnessAxioms : Array String :=
  axiomCoverageManifest

